gomodel:SYNGO_1716  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.5 SAPAP 4 is enriched in PSD\nLiteral \"We found that SAPAP1, -3, and -4 were all highly enriched in PSD fractions.\"\n\nFig. 8 SAPAP 4 is expressed at neuronal cholinergic synapses.\nLiteral \"SAPAP1, -3, and -4 were highly enriched at synapses in the submandibular ganglion, as demonstrated by simultaneously staining the sections for the presynaptic marker protein synaptophysin (Fig. 8B,D,F).\n\nFig. 11 SAPAP 4 proteins colocalizes with PSD-95.\nLiteral \" As a positive control, the same experiments were performed\nusing double labeling with the NMDA receptor binding protein, PSD-95. SAPAP1, -3, and -4 all showed extensive colocalization with PSD-95 (Fig. 11), implying,\nas expected, that SAPAP1, -3, and -4 were located at glutamatergic synapses in the spinal cord.\". Experimental description: All the experiments were done in mouse\nLiteral \"P21-P28 mice were deeply anesthetized with halothane\nand perfused transcardially with lactated Ringer's solution. The PSD fraction of whole mouse brain was prepared as described\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1716" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

